1. Edit the files
   BuildConfig.txt
   and
   CMakeLists.txt
   to select the cluster environment and the compiler.
   
2. If you have changed the files, then call
   rm CMakeCache.txt
   rm -r CMakeFiles/
   in order to ensure that the files are re-read by cmake.
   
3. Run 
   cmake .
   to let cmake create a make-file for the environment.
  
4. Run 
   make or make.openmpi (on ITP-Cluster)
